'''Connexion''' is an alternative British English spelling of the word [[Connection (disambiguation)|connection]]<ref>Soanes, Catherine and Stevenson, Angus (ed.) (2005). ''Oxford Dictionary of English'', 2nd Ed., revised, Oxford University Press, Oxford, New York, p. 367., ISBN 978-0-19-861057-1.</ref> and may refer to:

* [[Connexionalism]], a system of ecclesiastical polity
* [[Connexion by Boeing]], an in-flight online connectivity service
* [[PhyQuest Connexion]], a risk-reduction reporting system
* [[The Connexion]], a monthly English-language newspaper for English-speakers in France
* "Connexion", a track on [[Late Night Tales: Matt Helders]] DJ mix album
* [[Connexions]], a repository of educational materials started at Rice University
* [[Connexions (agency)]], a support service in the United Kingdom
* [[ConneXions Leadership Academy]], a middle school in Baltimore, Maryland
* [[Connexions (website)]], a website for the movements for social change in Canada

